--  GPIO-matrix signal indices for the ESP32-S3, mirroring ESP-IDF's authoritative
--  soc/esp32s3/include/soc/gpio_sig_map.h (IDF v5.4.3).  A signal index selects a
--  peripheral signal in the GPIO matrix: for OUTPUT signals via FUNC_OUT_SEL_CFG
--  (which signal drives a pad) and for INPUT signals via FUNC_IN_SEL_CFG (which pad
--  feeds a peripheral).  The two directions share one 0..256 numbering space, so an
--  index can name BOTH an output and an input signal (e.g. 166 = PWM1_OUT0A output
--  AND PWM0_CAP0 input) -- the _OUT/_IN suffix disambiguates.  256 = SIG_GPIO_OUT
--  (drive the pad's own GPIO output).
--
--  Generated from the IDF header (drop each name's trailing "_IDX"; the metadata
--  define GPIO_MAP_DATE is omitted).  Re-derive rather than hand-edit.

